# FitTrack App - Versioning History

This document describes the semantic versioning of the FitTrack app, a fitness tracking mobile application.

## Version 1.0.0
- Initial release with core features:
  - User account creation.
  - Daily steps and calories tracking.
  - Basic workout and meal logging.
  - Dashboard to track weekly activity.

## Version 1.1.0
- New features:
  - Integration with wearable devices.
  - Predefined workout plans.
  - Enhanced meal logging.
- Performance improvements and UI tweaks.

## Version 1.1.3
- Bug fixes:
  - Resolved issues with wearable syncing.
  - Fixed app crashes during logout.
  - Corrected calorie-tracking issues.

## Version 1.2.0
- New features:
  - Social sharing for achievements.
  - Leaderboard feature.
  - Added macro-nutrient breakdown for meal logging.
- Improved step-tracking accuracy.

## Version 2.0.0
- Major release:
  - Full app redesign.
  - AI-based workout recommendations.
  - Premium subscription features.
  - Video tutorials for exercises.
  - Deprecated older device support.

## Version 2.0.1
- Bug fixes:
  - Fixed subscription access issues.
  - Resolved video loading problems.

---
This README was created as part of the exercise on semantic versioning.
